you had better have it, if any one should 
want anything." 

^^Who is there to want anything?" 
Gertrude demanded. ^*I shall be all alone 
in the house." 

"Some one may come," said her com- 
panion. 

" Do you mean Mr. Brand ? " 

"Yes, Gertrude. He may like a piece 
of cake." 

" I don't like men that are always eating 
cake!" Gertrude declared, giving a pull at 
the lilac-buish. 

Her companion glanced at her, and then 
