relished highly, on occasions, the sense of 
being alone — the absence of the whole 
family and the emptiness of the house. 
To-day, apparently, the servants had also 
gone to church : there was never a figure 
at the open windows; behind the house 
there was no stout negress in a red turban, 
lowering the bucket into the great shingle- 
hooded well. And the front door of the 
