for the moment, to the coldly brilliant 
category of unattainable possessions. She 
was not the first woman for whom he had 
entertained an unpractical admiration. He 
had been in love with duchesses and 
countesses, and he had made, once or twice, 
a perilously near approach to cynicism in 
declaring that the disinterestedness of women 
had been overrated. On the whole he had 
tempered audacity with modesty ; and it is 
but fair to him, now, to say explicitly that 
he would have been incapable of takmg 
