rather young; but the younger one begins, 
I think, the better. Now, at any rate, you 
have no time to lose, and when I return you 
must immediately come to me." 

All this, to Clifford's apprehension, was 
a great mixture — his beginning young, 
Eugenia's return to Europe, his being 
introduced to her charming little circle. 
What was he to begin, and what was her little 
