so delicate!" And, in the dim light, he 
continued to smile intensely. " You know I 
take a great interest in my cousins — in 
Charlotte and Gertrude Wentworth. That's 
very evident from my ha\4ng travelled some 
five thousand miles to see them." Mr. 



X.] , 295 

Brand said nothing and Felix proceeded. 
*^ Coming into their society as a perfect 
stranger I received of course a great many 
new impressions, and my impressions had a 
great freshness, a great keenness. Do you 
know what T mean ? " 

"I am not sure that I do; but I should 
like you to continue." 

*^I think my impressions have always a 
