wanted to say. " What do you mean by 
Miss Gertrude being strong?" he asked, 
abruptly. 

" Well," said Felix meditatively, " I mean 
that she has had a great deal of self-posses- 
sion. She was waiting — for years; even 
when she seemed, perhaps, to be living in 
the present. She knew how to wait; she 
had a purpose. That's what I mean by her 
being strong." 

" But what do you mean by her purpose ? ** 

■^ Well — the purpose to see the world ! " 

Mr. Brand eyed his strange informant 

askance again; but he said nothing. At 

last he turned away, as if to take leave. He 

seemed bewildered, however; for instead of 



X.] . 303 

going to the door he moved toward the 
