He went on with her in silence ; he was 
much more affected by what she had told 
him than appeared. Ever since that evening 
of his return from Newport her image had 
had a terrible power to trouble him. What 
Clifford Wentworth had told him — that had 
affected him, too, in an adverse sense; but 
