sitting there in unillumined perplexity. 

Felix did no work that day. In the 
afternoon, with Gertrude, he got into one 
of the boats, and floated about with idly- 
dipping oars. They talked a good deal of 
Mr. Brand — ^though not exclusively. 

"That was a fine stroke," said Felix. " It 
was really heroic." 

Gertrude sat musing, with her eyes 
upon the ripples. "That was what he 
wanted to be; he wanted to do something 
fine.^V 

"He won^t be comfortable till he has 



